<annotation id="annotation_1667917745" type="text" style="popup" log_data="a-id=annotation_1667917745&amp;a-type=1&amp;xble=1&amp;a-v=twcHuKYR0pY&amp;ei=wbceXNTiMtLa8gTni5boAg" itct="CAMQs-UBGP___________wEiEwiUx6W7u7TfAhVSrZwKHeeFBS0o-B0yAml2SJalx7CK98GDtwE">
  <TEXT>Even though it should be somewhat obvious due to the nature of this stage: Don&#39;t stand near any enemy that emits those circular explosions upon death. They can actually hurt you if you run into them (which I find is complete BS, in all honesty).</TEXT>
  <segment>
    <movingRegion type="rect">
      <rectRegion x="0.00000" y="0.00000" w="100.00000" h="20.98600" t="3:49.228"/>
      <rectRegion x="0.00000" y="0.00000" w="100.00000" h="20.98600" t="4:00.200"/>
    </movingRegion>
  </segment>
  <appearance bgAlpha="0.600000023842" bgColor="0" fgColor="16777215" textSize="3.911599999999999" effects="">
    
  </appearance>
  
</annotation>
<annotation id="annotation_1758815399" type="text" style="popup" log_data="a-id=annotation_1758815399&amp;a-type=1&amp;xble=1&amp;a-v=twcHuKYR0pY&amp;ei=wbceXNTiMtLa8gTni5boAg" itct="CAQQs-UBGP___________wEiEwiUx6W7u7TfAhVSrZwKHeeFBS0o-B0yAml2SJalx7CK98GDtwE">
  <TEXT>This fight tries to utilize the shot-reflecting mechanics from the last few rooms. Despite this, you can just as easily hit this boss with a fully charged shot while at the peak of your jump. This isn&#39;t the last we&#39;ll be seeing of this gimmick, however.</TEXT>
  <segment>
    <movingRegion type="rect">
      <rectRegion x="0.00000" y="0.00000" w="100.00000" h="20.71800" t="2:13.839"/>
      <rectRegion x="0.00000" y="0.00000" w="100.00000" h="20.71800" t="2:25.800"/>
    </movingRegion>
  </segment>
  <appearance bgAlpha="0.600000023842" bgColor="0" fgColor="16777215" textSize="3.911599999999999" effects="">
    
  </appearance>
  
</annotation>
<annotation id="annotation_1764960059" type="text" style="popup" log_data="a-id=annotation_1764960059&amp;a-type=1&amp;xble=1&amp;a-v=twcHuKYR0pY&amp;ei=wbceXNTiMtLa8gTni5boAg" itct="CAUQs-UBGP___________wEiEwiUx6W7u7TfAhVSrZwKHeeFBS0o-B0yAml2SJalx7CK98GDtwE">
  <TEXT>Also, be extremely careful with your shots while around those mine carts. Had I not scrolled the screen back, I may have risked hitting the switch for the next one. From what I can tell, they don&#39;t respawn either.</TEXT>
  <segment>
    <movingRegion type="rect">
      <rectRegion x="0.00000" y="0.00000" w="100.00000" h="20.70400" t="4:42.818"/>
      <rectRegion x="0.00000" y="0.00000" w="100.00000" h="20.70400" t="4:51.800"/>
    </movingRegion>
  </segment>
  <appearance bgAlpha="0.600000023842" bgColor="0" fgColor="16777215" textSize="3.911599999999999" effects="">
    
  </appearance>
  
</annotation>
<annotation id="annotation_1769530339" type="text" style="popup" log_data="a-id=annotation_1769530339&amp;a-type=1&amp;xble=1&amp;a-v=twcHuKYR0pY&amp;ei=wbceXNTiMtLa8gTni5boAg" itct="CAYQs-UBGP___________wEiEwiUx6W7u7TfAhVSrZwKHeeFBS0o-B0yAml2SJalx7CK98GDtwE">
  <TEXT>In terms of physical design, the RM&#39;s in this game are a bit more interesting than the ones in Revolution. The best part about them however, is that most of the weapons you get from them are actually really good!</TEXT>
  <segment>
    <movingRegion type="rect">
      <rectRegion x="0.00000" y="0.00000" w="100.00000" h="20.70400" t="3:10.423"/>
      <rectRegion x="0.00000" y="0.00000" w="100.00000" h="20.70400" t="3:19.400"/>
    </movingRegion>
  </segment>
  <appearance bgAlpha="0.600000023842" bgColor="0" fgColor="16777215" textSize="3.911599999999999" effects="">
    
  </appearance>
  
</annotation>
<annotation id="annotation_2034196387" type="text" style="popup" log_data="a-id=annotation_2034196387&amp;a-type=1&amp;xble=1&amp;a-v=twcHuKYR0pY&amp;ei=wbceXNTiMtLa8gTni5boAg" itct="CAcQs-UBGP___________wEiEwiUx6W7u7TfAhVSrZwKHeeFBS0o-B0yAml2SJalx7CK98GDtwE">
  <TEXT>Just to note: Unlike in Street Fighter X Mega Man, you don&#39;t need full health to get this bonus. You just need to avoid taking a hit once you&#39;re in the boss room, no matter what your health is at.</TEXT>
  <segment>
    <movingRegion type="rect">
      <rectRegion x="0.00000" y="0.00000" w="100.00000" h="20.70400" t="7:00.756"/>
      <rectRegion x="0.00000" y="0.00000" w="100.00000" h="20.70400" t="7:09.800"/>
    </movingRegion>
  </segment>
  <appearance bgAlpha="0.600000023842" bgColor="0" fgColor="16777215" textSize="3.911599999999999" effects="">
    
  </appearance>
  
</annotation>
<annotation id="annotation_2062135751" type="text" style="popup" log_data="a-id=annotation_2062135751&amp;a-type=1&amp;xble=1&amp;a-v=twcHuKYR0pY&amp;ei=wbceXNTiMtLa8gTni5boAg" itct="CAgQs-UBGP___________wEiEwiUx6W7u7TfAhVSrZwKHeeFBS0o-B0yAml2SJalx7CK98GDtwE">
  <TEXT>As you might be able to guess, this area has a small time-limit. Despite it being an instant kill if the timer reaches 0, you don&#39;t have much to worry here. The game gives you more than enough time to make it to the end.</TEXT>
  <segment>
    <movingRegion type="rect">
      <rectRegion x="0.00000" y="0.00000" w="100.00000" h="20.43700" t="5:45.611"/>
      <rectRegion x="0.00000" y="0.00000" w="100.00000" h="20.43700" t="5:56.600"/>
    </movingRegion>
  </segment>
  <appearance bgAlpha="0.600000023842" bgColor="0" fgColor="16777215" textSize="3.911599999999999" effects="">
    
  </appearance>
  
</annotation>
<annotation id="annotation_2405194615" type="text" style="popup" log_data="a-id=annotation_2405194615&amp;a-type=1&amp;xble=1&amp;a-v=twcHuKYR0pY&amp;ei=wbceXNTiMtLa8gTni5boAg" itct="CAkQs-UBGP___________wEiEwiUx6W7u7TfAhVSrZwKHeeFBS0o-B0yAml2SJalx7CK98GDtwE">
  <TEXT>While the Robot Masters in this game are certainly better looking than the ones in Revolution...they&#39;re also vastly easier in comparison. Sadly, there&#39;s very few bosses in this game that pose any kind of threat.</TEXT>
  <segment>
    <movingRegion type="rect">
      <rectRegion x="0.00000" y="0.00000" w="100.00000" h="21.28200" t="6:16.096"/>
      <rectRegion x="0.00000" y="0.00000" w="100.00000" h="21.28200" t="6:25.100"/>
    </movingRegion>
  </segment>
  <appearance bgAlpha="0.600000023842" bgColor="0" fgColor="16777215" textSize="3.911599999999999" effects="">
    
  </appearance>
  
</annotation>
<annotation id="annotation_2874371413" type="text" style="popup" log_data="a-id=annotation_2874371413&amp;a-type=1&amp;xble=1&amp;a-v=twcHuKYR0pY&amp;ei=wbceXNTiMtLa8gTni5boAg" itct="CAoQs-UBGP___________wEiEwiUx6W7u7TfAhVSrZwKHeeFBS0o-B0yAml2SJalx7CK98GDtwE">
  <TEXT>There is one interesting thing to note on these fights, however: If you beat a Robot Master without taking a hit, you&#39;ll get a &quot;Perfect Part&quot; along with their weapon. If you get all 4, you get access to Beat - somewhat akin to Mega Man 5.</TEXT>
  <segment>
    <movingRegion type="rect">
      <rectRegion x="0.00000" y="0.00000" w="100.00000" h="20.43700" t="6:50.045"/>
      <rectRegion x="0.00000" y="0.00000" w="100.00000" h="20.43700" t="6:59.000"/>
    </movingRegion>
  </segment>
  <appearance bgAlpha="0.600000023842" bgColor="0" fgColor="16777215" textSize="3.911599999999999" effects="">
    
  </appearance>
  
</annotation>
<annotation id="annotation_293280037" type="text" style="popup" log_data="a-id=annotation_293280037&amp;a-type=1&amp;xble=1&amp;a-v=twcHuKYR0pY&amp;ei=wbceXNTiMtLa8gTni5boAg" itct="">
  <TEXT>Just a slight heads up: You should begin bracing yourself for some of the worst pixel-art ever. It&#39;s another reason as to why I skipped most of these opening cutscenes...</TEXT>
  <segment>
    <movingRegion type="rect">
      <rectRegion x="0.00000" y="0.00000" w="100.00000" h="16.49300" t="2:49.691"/>
      <rectRegion x="0.00000" y="0.00000" w="100.00000" h="16.49300" t="2:56.700"/>
    </movingRegion>
  </segment>
  <appearance bgAlpha="0.600000023842" bgColor="0" fgColor="16777215" textSize="3.911599999999999" effects="">
    
  </appearance>
  
</annotation>
<annotation id="annotation_3055625999" type="text" style="popup" log_data="a-id=annotation_3055625999&amp;a-type=1&amp;xble=1&amp;a-v=twcHuKYR0pY&amp;ei=wbceXNTiMtLa8gTni5boAg" itct="">
  <TEXT>As said before, Phantom Fuse is the best weapon in the game. The demonstration here isn&#39;t an exageration, either. It outright annihilates nearly every non-boss enemy in the game with just one shot.</TEXT>
  <segment>
    <movingRegion type="rect">
      <rectRegion x="0.00000" y="75.49300" w="100.00000" h="21.00000" t="7:15.700"/>
      <rectRegion x="0.00000" y="75.49300" w="100.00000" h="21.00000" t="7:26.700"/>
    </movingRegion>
  </segment>
  <appearance bgAlpha="0.600000023842" bgColor="0" fgColor="16777215" textSize="3.911599999999999" effects="">
    
  </appearance>
  
</annotation>
<annotation id="annotation_3258072075" type="text" style="popup" log_data="a-id=annotation_3258072075&amp;a-type=1&amp;xble=1&amp;a-v=twcHuKYR0pY&amp;ei=wbceXNTiMtLa8gTni5boAg" itct="">
  <TEXT>Anyways, let&#39;s start with the basic mechanics of this game:
Mega Man himself retains his primary abilities from 4 - 8, meaning he can both slide and charge. You also start out with an Energy Balancer, strangely enough.</TEXT>
  <segment>
    <movingRegion type="rect">
      <rectRegion x="0.00000" y="0.00000" w="100.00000" h="20.71800" t="0:36.816"/>
      <rectRegion x="0.00000" y="0.00000" w="100.00000" h="20.71800" t="0:46.800"/>
    </movingRegion>
  </segment>
  <appearance bgAlpha="0.600000023842" bgColor="0" fgColor="16777215" textSize="3.911599999999999" effects="">
    
  </appearance>
  
</annotation>
<annotation id="annotation_3791357933" type="text" style="popup" log_data="a-id=annotation_3791357933&amp;a-type=1&amp;xble=1&amp;a-v=twcHuKYR0pY&amp;ei=wbceXNTiMtLa8gTni5boAg" itct="">
  <TEXT>You also start out with three support weapons in the form of Rush, Eddie, and Tango. Rush has the standard Coil ability, Eddie gives you any item at random (including potential E-Tanks), and Tango rolls on the ground to attack enemies.</TEXT>
  <segment>
    <movingRegion type="rect">
      <rectRegion x="0.00000" y="0.00000" w="100.00000" h="21.28200" t="0:49.224"/>
      <rectRegion x="0.00000" y="0.00000" w="100.00000" h="21.28200" t="1:00.200"/>
    </movingRegion>
  </segment>
  <appearance bgAlpha="0.600000023842" bgColor="0" fgColor="16777215" textSize="3.911599999999999" effects="">
    
  </appearance>
  
</annotation>
<annotation id="annotation_4022778263" type="text" style="popup" log_data="a-id=annotation_4022778263&amp;a-type=1&amp;xble=1&amp;a-v=twcHuKYR0pY&amp;ei=wbceXNTiMtLa8gTni5boAg" itct="">
  <TEXT>Spikes in this game act like Mega Man 1 spikes (although I think this is just an oversight on the programmer&#39;s part). If you touch them, even with invincibility frames, you&#39;ll still die.</TEXT>
  <segment>
    <movingRegion type="rect">
      <rectRegion x="0.00000" y="0.00000" w="100.00000" h="15.93000" t="1:15.880"/>
      <rectRegion x="0.00000" y="0.00000" w="100.00000" h="15.93000" t="1:24.900"/>
    </movingRegion>
  </segment>
  <appearance bgAlpha="0.600000023842" bgColor="0" fgColor="16777215" textSize="3.911599999999999" effects="">
    
  </appearance>
  
</annotation>
<annotation id="annotation_558574873" type="text" style="popup" log_data="a-id=annotation_558574873&amp;a-type=1&amp;xble=1&amp;a-v=twcHuKYR0pY&amp;ei=wbceXNTiMtLa8gTni5boAg" itct="">
  <TEXT>Just to note, I&#39;m skipping the opening story for this game, since...well, you really don&#39;t need to be put through the rather terrible story-line for this (and the awful pixel-art for the cutscenes). If you&#39;re really curious, I&#39;ll elaborate it in brief in the description.</TEXT>
  <segment>
    <movingRegion type="rect">
      <rectRegion x="0.00000" y="0.00000" w="100.00000" h="24.94400" t="0:12.635"/>
      <rectRegion x="0.00000" y="0.00000" w="100.00000" h="24.94400" t="0:23.600"/>
    </movingRegion>
  </segment>
  <appearance bgAlpha="0.600000023842" bgColor="0" fgColor="16777215" textSize="3.911599999999999" effects="">
    
  </appearance>
  
</annotation>
<annotation id="annotation_804559653" type="text" style="popup" log_data="a-id=annotation_804559653&amp;a-type=1&amp;xble=1&amp;a-v=twcHuKYR0pY&amp;ei=wbceXNTiMtLa8gTni5boAg" itct="">
  <TEXT>Crypt Man&#39;s weapon will allow you to walk on those translucent platforms. While it&#39;s not necessary to use them in some of these levels, it really does help out in a few instances.</TEXT>
  <segment>
    <movingRegion type="rect">
      <rectRegion x="0.00000" y="0.00000" w="100.00000" h="16.21100" t="4:15.896"/>
      <rectRegion x="0.00000" y="0.00000" w="100.00000" h="16.21100" t="4:24.900"/>
    </movingRegion>
  </segment>
  <appearance bgAlpha="0.600000023842" bgColor="0" fgColor="16777215" textSize="3.911599999999999" effects="">
    
  </appearance>
  
</annotation>
<annotation id="annotation_950804685" type="text" style="popup" log_data="a-id=annotation_950804685&amp;a-type=1&amp;xble=1&amp;a-v=twcHuKYR0pY&amp;ei=wbceXNTiMtLa8gTni5boAg" itct="">
  <TEXT>Now that I&#39;ve completely put off Eons of Dreams for the garbage heap that it is, it&#39;s time to play something that&#39;s actually not half-bad.</TEXT>
  <segment>
    <movingRegion type="rect">
      <rectRegion x="0.00000" y="0.00000" w="100.00000" h="15.93000" t="0:00.635"/>
